Former All Progressives Congress Publicity Secretary in Lagos State, Joe Igbokwe has stated that the 2023 election will not be won on social media platforms.
The Special Adviser to Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu on Drainages and Water Resources added that former Lagos State Governor, Asiwaju Bola Ahmed has touched millions of Nigerians one way or the other.

Joe Igbokwe, who hails from Anambra State in the South East region of the country said those that Tinubu has touched for close to 40 years will pay him back in 2023.
Bola Ahmed Tinubu who is the National Leader of the All Progressives Congress (APC) and former Lagos State Governor is one of those vying for President of Nigeria in 2023.
The APC chieftain has informed President Muhammadu Buhari of his intention to succeed him next year. He has also been visiting influential Nigerians informing them of his aspiration.
